<section class='settings-container max-w-3xl mx-auto'>
    <p class='text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2'>
        <a class='text-link' href='/developer'>← Developer Portal</a>
    </p>
    <h1 class='page-title'>Tutorial: Build an AI Collection Assistant with the MCP Server</h1>
    <p class='text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6'>
        The <a class='text-link' href='https://github.com/matthewdtowles/iwantmymtg-mcp' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>iwantmymtg-mcp</a>
        server connects Claude to your IWMM collection, so you can look up cards, log what you own,
        check what it is worth, and set price alerts just by asking. This walkthrough takes you from
        zero to a real conversation in about ten minutes.
    </p>

    <div class='space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300'>

        <div>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>What you'll build</h2>
            <p>
                By the end you will have Claude Desktop wired to your account and will run one
                conversation that touches both read tools and write tools: find a card and its
                price, add copies to your inventory, see your portfolio value, and set an alert for a
                price drop. The same setup works in Claude Code and Cursor.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul class='list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>
                <li>An IWMM account - <a class='text-link' href='/auth/register'>sign up</a> if you do not have one.</li>
                <li>An API key from <a class='text-link' href='/user/api-keys'>/user/api-keys</a>. The raw key is shown only once, so copy it somewhere safe.</li>
                <li>Claude Desktop (or Claude Code / Cursor) and Node 20 or newer.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class='mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>
                The Free tier gives you 100 requests/day, which is plenty for this tutorial. See
                <a class='text-link' href='/developer/pricing'>API pricing</a> for higher limits.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>1. Add the server to Claude Desktop</h2>
            <p class='mb-2'>
                Open <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>claude_desktop_config.json</code>
                (macOS: <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>;
                Windows: <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json</code>)
                and add the <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>iwmm</code> server, pasting your key in place of <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>iwm_live_...</code>:
            </p>
            <pre class='bg-gray-900 text-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 text-xs overflow-x-auto'><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "iwmm": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "iwantmymtg-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "IWMM_API_KEY": "iwm_live_..."
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
            <p class='mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>
                Save the file and restart Claude Desktop. The first launch downloads the package via
                <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>npx</code>, so give it a few seconds. This snippet is the
                same one in the <a class='text-link' href='https://github.com/matthewdtowles/iwantmymtg-mcp#claude-desktop' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>repository README</a>;
                if they ever differ, the README is the source of truth.
            </p>
            <p class='mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>
                Prefer Claude Code or Cursor? The same block goes in <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>.mcp.json</code>
                or <code class='bg-gray-100 dark:bg-midnight-700 px-1 rounded'>.cursor/mcp.json</code>. The full setup for each client is in the
                <a class='text-link' href='/developer/guides/mcp-server'>MCP Server guide</a>.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>2. Confirm the tools loaded</h2>
            <p>
                In a new chat, ask Claude <em>"what iwmm tools do you have?"</em> It should list card
                and set lookups, inventory and transaction tools, portfolio breakdowns, and price
                alerts. If nothing shows up, double-check the JSON is valid and that you restarted the
                app after saving.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>3. A real walkthrough</h2>
            <p class='mb-4'>
                Here is a full exchange that exercises both read and write tools. Yours will read back
                slightly different prices, but the shape is the same.
            </p>

            <div class='space-y-4'>
                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 mb-1'>You</p>
                    <p>Find Lightning Bolt and show me the cheapest printing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-midnight-800 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1'>Claude
                        <span class='ml-1 font-normal normal-case text-gray-400'>· calls search_cards, get_card_prices</span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Lightning Bolt has dozens of printings. The cheapest in normal (non-foil) is the
                        Magic 2010 (M10) printing at about $1.20. The original Alpha (LEA) printing is the
                        priciest. Want me to add one of these to your collection?
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 mb-1'>You</p>
                    <p>Add 4 copies of the M10 printing to my inventory.</p>
                </div>
                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-midnight-800 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1'>Claude
                        <span class='ml-1 font-normal normal-case text-gray-400'>· calls add_inventory</span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Done - added 4x Lightning Bolt (M10, non-foil) to your inventory. You now hold 4
                        copies, worth roughly $4.80 at the current price.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 mb-1'>You</p>
                    <p>What's my whole collection worth right now?</p>
                </div>
                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-midnight-800 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1'>Claude
                        <span class='ml-1 font-normal normal-case text-gray-400'>· calls get_portfolio_summary</span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Your collection is worth about $1,312 across 268 cards. The largest single
                        contributors are your Modern Horizons 3 cards. Want a breakdown by set?
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 mb-1'>You</p>
                    <p>Alert me if Lightning Bolt drops below $1.</p>
                </div>
                <div class='rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-midnight-800 p-4'>
                    <p class='text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1'>Claude
                        <span class='ml-1 font-normal normal-case text-gray-400'>· calls create_price_alert</span>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Set. I'll flag Lightning Bolt (M10) the next time its normal price falls below
                        $1.00. You can see and manage alerts on your IWMM notifications page.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>A note on writes</h2>
            <p>
                Inventory, transaction, and alert tools make real changes to your account - there is no
                dry-run mode in v1. Claude confirms before it writes, but treat it like running a
                command yourself: read what it proposes before approving. Read-only card, set, price,
                and portfolio lookups never change anything.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class='border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-midnight-700 pt-6'>
            <h2 class='text-lg font-semibold mb-2'>Where to go next</h2>
            <ul class='list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>
                <li>Source and issues: <a class='text-link' href='https://github.com/matthewdtowles/iwantmymtg-mcp' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>github.com/matthewdtowles/iwantmymtg-mcp</a></li>
                <li>npm package: <a class='text-link' href='https://www.npmjs.com/package/iwantmymtg-mcp' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>npmjs.com/package/iwantmymtg-mcp</a></li>
                <li>Per-client setup and the full tool list: <a class='text-link' href='/developer/guides/mcp-server'>MCP Server guide</a></li>
                <li>Prefer raw HTTP? The same data is in the <a class='text-link' href='/developer/docs'>API reference</a>.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
